# Zephyria VM & Smart Contract Platform: Comprehensive Analysis

> Deep-dive into RISC-V interpreter execution, smart contract platform completeness, architectural gaps, and 1M TPS linear scaling requirements.

---

## Part 1: RISC-V Interpreter — Execution Workflow Analysis

### 1.1 Interpreter Architecture Overview

The ZephVM is a **pure software interpreter** executing the **RV32EM** instruction set (32-bit RISC-V with M-extension, constrained to 16 registers). It is **not** a JIT compiler or AOT compiler — it runs a classic **fetch-decode-execute-gas loop**.

| Component | File | Role |
|---|---|---|
| **Decoder** | [decoder.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/core/decoder.zig) | Decodes 32-bit instruction words into 7 format variants |
| **Executor** | [executor.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/core/executor.zig) | Fetch-decode-execute loop, CPU state (16 regs + PC) |
| **Gas Meter** | [meter.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/gas/meter.zig) | Per-instruction + per-syscall gas tracking with EIP-3529 refunds |
| **Gas Table** | [table.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/gas/table.zig) | 128-entry opcode lookup + EIP-2929 syscall costs |
| **Sandbox Memory** | [sandbox.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/memory/sandbox.zig) | 640KB linear memory, 5 permission-enforced regions |
| **Syscall Dispatch** | [dispatch.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/syscall/dispatch.zig) | 35 syscalls bridging guest and host |
| **Contract Loader** | [contract_loader.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/loader/contract_loader.zig) | ELF parsing, .zeph verification, validation |
| **VM Pool** | [vm_pool.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/vm_pool.zig) | Pre-allocated sandbox buffers for zero-alloc reuse |
| **VM Bridge** | [vm_bridge.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/vm_bridge.zig) | Thread-safe bridge from DAG executor to RISC-V VM |

### 1.2 End-to-End Contract Execution Workflow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant User as User TX
    participant DAG as DAG Executor
    participant Bridge as VMBridge
    participant Loader as ContractLoader
    participant VM as ZephVM Executor
    participant Syscall as SyscallDispatch
    participant State as StateBridge / Overlay

    User->>DAG: Submit TX (to, data, gas)
    DAG->>DAG: Schedule TX into lane (zero-conflict)
    DAG->>Bridge: executeCallback(code, input, gas, overlay, caller, value)
    Bridge->>Bridge: Create StateBridge(overlay, caller, value)
    Bridge->>Bridge: Wire block/TX context (timestamp, coinbase, etc.)
    Bridge->>Loader: executeContract(code, input, gas, state_bridge)
    Loader->>Loader: Parse ELF / .zeph / raw bytecode
    Loader->>Loader: Validate (opcode scan, size check, alignment)
    Loader->>VM: ZephVM.init(sandbox, code_len, gas, handler)
    Loader->>VM: Load code into CODE region, calldata into CALLDATA region
    VM->>VM: Set PC = entry_point, SP = STACK_TOP

    loop Fetch-Decode-Execute-Gas
        VM->>VM: 1. Check PC bounds and step limit
        VM->>VM: 2. Fetch 32-bit word from CODE region
        VM->>VM: 3. Fast gas pre-check via opcode table
        VM->>VM: 4. Decode into R/I/S/B/U/J/System
        VM->>VM: 5. Charge M-ext extra gas (MUL=2, DIV=3)
        VM->>VM: 6. Dispatch and execute instruction
        VM->>VM: 7. Enforce x0 = 0
        VM->>VM: 8. Advance PC += 4 (unless branch/jump)
    end

    Note over VM,Syscall: On ECALL instruction
    VM->>Syscall: handler(vm) reads syscall ID from x15
    Syscall->>State: SLOAD/SSTORE via StateBridge to Overlay
    Syscall->>VM: Write results to registers/memory

    Note over VM: On RETURN/REVERT syscall
    VM->>VM: Set status = returned/reverted
    VM->>Loader: Return ExecutionResult
    Loader->>Bridge: Return ContractResult
    Bridge->>DAG: Return VMResult(success, gas_used, return_data)
    DAG->>DAG: Merge deltas + commit overlay
```

### 1.3 The Fetch-Decode-Execute-Gas Loop (Hot Path)

Every instruction goes through exactly **8 stages** in [executor.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/core/executor.zig#L136-L200):

| Stage | Operation | Cost | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | PC bounds check | ~1 ns | Validates `pc < code_len` and 4-byte alignment |
| 2 | Step limit check | ~1 ns | Defense-in-depth: max 10M steps per execution |
| 3 | Fetch instruction | ~1-3 ns | `memory.loadWord(pc)` — in L1 cache for hot loops |
| 4 | Fast gas pre-check | ~1 ns | 128-entry `OPCODE_GAS_TABLE[opcode]` lookup |
| 5 | Decode | ~2-5 ns | Pattern match on 7-bit opcode, extract fields |
| 6 | M-ext extra gas | conditional | Only for MUL/DIV: charges delta above ALU base |
| 7 | Dispatch and execute | ~2-15 ns | R/I/S/B/U/J/System handler |
| 8 | x0 enforcement + PC advance | ~1 ns | Hardwired zero + PC += 4 |

**Total per-instruction: ~10-25 ns, giving theoretical ~40-100M instructions/second** on a single core.

### 1.4 Guest to Host Bridge: The Syscall ABI

The RISC-V `ecall` instruction is the **only** bridge between guest (contract) and host (node). The ABI is:

| Register | Role |
|---|---|
| `x10-x14` (a0-a4) | Arguments |
| `x15` (a5) | Syscall ID |
| `x10-x11` (a0-a1) | Return values |

**35 implemented syscalls** covering:

| Category | Syscalls | EVM Equivalent |
|---|---|---|
| **Storage** | `SLOAD` (0x01), `SSTORE` (0x02) | `SLOAD`, `SSTORE` with EIP-2929/3529 |
| **Events** | `EMIT_EVENT` (0x03), `LOG_RAW` (0x12) | `LOG0`-`LOG4` |
| **Calls** | `CALL` (0x04), `DELEGATECALL` (0x05), `STATICCALL` (0x1C) | `CALL`, `DELEGATECALL`, `STATICCALL` |
| **Context** | `GET_CALLER` (0x06), `GET_CALLVALUE` (0x07), `GET_CALLDATA` (0x08), `GET_CALLDATA_SIZE` (0x13) | `CALLER`, `CALLVALUE`, `CALLDATACOPY`, `CALLDATASIZE` |
| **Control** | `RETURN` (0x09), `REVERT` (0x0A), `SELFDESTRUCT` (0x11) | `RETURN`, `REVERT`, `SELFDESTRUCT` |
| **Crypto** | `KECCAK256` (0x0B), `ECRECOVER` (0x1D) | `KECCAK256`, `ECRECOVER` |
| **Balance** | `GET_BALANCE` (0x0C) | `BALANCE` |
| **Block** | `BLOCKNUMBER`, `TIMESTAMP`, `CHAINID`, `COINBASE`, `BASEFEE`, `PREVRANDAO`, `GASLIMIT` | Full EVM parity |
| **Code** | `CODESIZE` (0x20), `CODECOPY` (0x21), `EXTCODESIZE` (0x22) | `CODESIZE`, `CODECOPY`, `EXTCODESIZE` |
| **Returns** | `RETURNDATASIZE` (0x1E), `RETURNDATACOPY` (0x1F) | `RETURNDATASIZE`, `RETURNDATACOPY` |
| **Deploy** | `CREATE_CONTRACT` (0x10) | `CREATE` |

### 1.5 SDK Runtime: Contract Entry Point Lifecycle

The SDK in [riscv_runtime.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/src/sdk/riscv_runtime.zig) implements the guest-side lifecycle:

```
_start (naked ASM)
  |
  +-> riscvMain()
       |-- 1. ecall GET_CALLDATA_SIZE -> cd_size
       |-- 2. ecall GET_CALLDATA -> calldata_buf[0..cd_size]
       |-- 3. ExecutionContext.fromHost() -> ecalls GET_CALLER, GET_CALLVALUE, etc.
       |-- 4. Dispatch: extract selector (first 4 bytes) -> match handler
       |-- 5. Execute handler logic (SLOAD/SSTORE via ecall)
       +-- 6. ecall RETURN_DATA or REVERT -> halt VM
```

### 1.6 Sandbox Memory Layout

The [sandbox.zig](file:///Users/karan/sol2zig/vm/memory/sandbox.zig) enforces a strict 640KB memory map:

| Region | Address Range | Size | Permissions |
|---|---|---|---|
| **Code** | `0x00000-0x0FFFF` | 64 KB | Read + Execute |
| **Heap** | `0x10000-0x4FFFF` | 256 KB | Read + Write |
| **Stack** | `0x50000-0x5FFFF` | 64 KB | Read + Write |
| **Calldata** | `0x60000-0x6FFFF` | 64 KB | Read Only |
| **Return** | `0x70000-0x9FFFF` | 192 KB | Read + Write |

> [!IMPORTANT]
> At ~640KB, the entire sandbox fits in L2 cache. This is critical for 1M TPS — no main memory round-trips during execution.

